subSubSection.paragraph:
This is a common species on both coasts of Grande Terre and the Central Range, Loyalty and Belep Islands, Isle of Pines and Walpole Island . It is also known from Australia . This is a polyphagous predator in natural habitats but also rangeland and disturbed areas. Recorded prey are cicadellid larvae, psyllids [
Heteropsylla cubana Crawford
,
Mesohomotoma hibisci (Froggatt)
], aphids (
Cerataphis
spp.), and lepidopterous eggs [
Spodoptera mauritia (Boisduval)
]. Its biology has been studied in New Caledonia by
Sallée & Chazeau ( 1985 )
in the context of biocontrol usage against two aphids [
Rhopalosiphum padi (Linnaeus)
and
Hyperomyzus lactucae (Linnaeus)
]. To date, this species has not yet been promoted for biocontrol programs.
